Osun State Polytechnic, Iree, has said its Rector, Dr Jacob Olusola Agboola, is not involved in certificate forgery. In a statement, its Registrar, B.M Salawu, said the Rector’s academic credentials were not in doubt. The institution urged the public not to confuse Agboola for another person. The statement absolved Agboola of having been involved in any certificate scandal. It stated that Agboola obtained his first degree from Ahmadu Bello University (ABU), Zaria, (1989) Masters from University of Nigeria (UNN) Nsukka (1992) and  Ladoke Akintola University (2002), and Ph.D from  Nnamdi Azikwe University, Awka (2006). 